Dataset Information

This lab uses two image sources for performing Neural Style Transfer:

1. CIFAR-10 Dataset (Content Image)

The CIFAR-10 dataset is a widely used benchmark dataset in computer vision. It contains 60,000 color images divided into 10 object categories, with 50,000 images for training and 10,000 images for testing. Each image has a resolution of 32 × 32 pixels and consists of three color channels (RGB).

The dataset includes the following classes:

Airplane

Automobile

Bird

Cat

Deer

Dog

Frog

Horse

Ship

Truck

In this lab, a single image from the CIFAR-10 dataset is used as the content image. The structural features of this image (objects, shapes, and layout) are preserved during the style transfer process.
